info.name: Video Understanding
info.description:
# üìπ Video Understanding with Gemini API Gemini models are built for **multimodal reasoning**, including powerful capabilities for **video understanding**. Developers can use Gemini to: - Describe, segment, and extract information from videos - Answer questions about video content - Refer to specific timestamps within a video (e.g., `01:30`) This guide shows how to provide video inputs to Gemini and generate meaningful text-based outputs. --- ## üîß Supported Video Input Methods You can pass video inputs to Gemini in **three ways**: ### 1. Upload a Video File (via File API) Use this for: - Videos **larger than 20MB** - Videos **longer than ~1 minute** - Reusable files across multiple requests --- ### 2. Pass Inline Video Data Use this for: - Files **under 20MB** - Shorter videos - Quick, one-off requests > ‚ö†Ô∏è If you receive `Argument list too long`, switch to the File API method. --- ### 3. Include a YouTube URL **Preview feature** ‚Äî available at no cost for now. Use this for: - Public videos only - Quick summarization and Q&A tasks --- ## ‚è± Timestamp Referencing You can ask about specific parts of the video using the `MM:SS` format: ```text What are the examples shown at 00:05 and 00:10? ``` --- ## üìù Transcription and Visual Descriptions Gemini transcribes audio and describes visuals by sampling 1 frame per second. --- ## üéõ Custom Video Processing ### Clip Video Segments Use `video_metadata` to process just part of the video: ```python video_metadata = types.VideoMetadata(start_offset='1250s', end_offset='1570s') ``` ### Set Custom Frame Rate Control detail level with `fps` in `video_metadata`: ```python video_metadata = types.VideoMetadata(fps=5) ``` - **Default FPS**: 1 - **Higher FPS**: For fast-changing visuals - **Lower FPS (<1)**: For long/static videos (e.g., lectures) --- ## ‚úÖ Supported Video Formats Gemini accepts the following MIME types: - `video/mp4` - `video/mpeg` - `video/mov` - `video/avi` - `video/x-flv` - `video/mpg` - `video/webm` - `video/wmv` - `video/3gpp` --- ## ‚öô Technical Details | Property | Description | |---------|-------------| | **Model Support** | All Gemini 2.0 and 2.5 models | | **Context Window** | 1M ‚Üí ~1 hr (default), 3 hrs (low res)
2M ‚Üí ~2 hrs (default), 6 hrs (low res) | | **File API Sampling** | 1 FPS (video), 1 Kbps (audio) | | **Token Usage** | 300 tokens/sec (default)
100 tokens/sec (low res) | | **Timestamp Format** | `MM:SS` |

request.description:
### üì∫ YouTube URL Support (Preview)

The Gemini API and AI Studio support **YouTube URLs** as a valid `file_data` input. You can include a YouTube video link alongside your prompt to ask the model to **summarize**, **translate**, or otherwise **analyze** the video content.

#### üîí Limitations

- **Free tier**: Limited to **8 hours of video per day**
- **Paid tier**: No limit based on video length
- **Model versions**:
  - Models **before 2.5**: Only **1 video** per request
  - Models **2.5 and later**: Up to **10 videos** per request
- Only **public** videos are supported ‚Äî **private** or **unlisted** videos are not allowed
